John Alechenu, Abuja Governors under the aegis of the Nigeria Governors Forum will today (Wednesday) hold its 12th teleconference since the outbreak of COVID-19. Top on the agenda are the Executive Order 10, which grants financial autonomy to the legislature and the judiciary in states, as well as Nigeria’s economic sustainability, post COVID-19, with special attention to the Nigeria Sovereign Investment Authority, among others. An invitation to the meeting, which was signed by the Director-General of the NGF, Mr AsishanaOkauru, added that other issues to be discussed included an update from the Governor of Delta State, Ifeanyi Okowa, and his committee’s interface with the Presidential Task Force on COVID-19. This was contained in a statement by the NGFs Head, Media and Public Affairs, Abdulrazaque Bello-Barkindo, in Abuja on Tuesday. It read in part, “The meeting takes place tomorrow, Wednesday, 8th of July 2020, and commences at 2pm. Governors are expected to start joining the meeting from  pm as it starts at 2pm.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com   